iHere's a quick note on special sauce needed for openbsd:		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i- clone from source as there's no package		gopher.black	70
i- make sure to install a bunch of perl dependencies listed in the		gopher.black	70
i  INSTALL file. It makes heavy use of these during make		gopher.black	70
i- use gmake not make if you can		gopher.black	70
i- configure --without-openssl is a must. The specific requirements		gopher.black	70
i  for TLS don't play nice with libssl		gopher.black	70
i- once you make install the paths will not be /etc/news and		gopher.black	70
i  /var/lib/news but rather /usr/local/news/etc and		gopher.black	70
i  /usr/local/news/db respectively.		gopher.black	70
i- innd won't start automatically. You'll need to change to the		gopher.black	70
i  "news" user and run /usr/local/news/bin/rc.news start.		gopher.black	70
i  I installed sudo to do it since my news user is non-login.		gopher.black	70
i- /usr/local/news/bin is also the path to ctlinnd, which you need		gopher.black	70
i  to install groups and restart the innd process.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iOtherwise the setup was pretty much the same as in my previous		gopher.black	70
ipost. Very cool.		gopher.black	70
